		"description": "<p>Beginning at level 6, your subtle ways extend to your actual use of magic, rather than merely the activities around it. When you cast a spell from the <em>obscurement </em>school, you may double its normal duration. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier, recovering all uses upon finishing a short or long rest.</p>\n<p>Also, when given time, you can conceal your spellcasting altogether. When casting a spell, you may make a Deception check to conceal the spell&rsquo;s origin. A creature attempting to determine where a spell came from must beat the result of this check with a Wisdom (Insight) check to know you cast the spell.</p>",
